natural solution: For any angle $x$, we have $\cos(180^\circ - x)=-\cos x$, so $\cos \angle RPS = \cos(180^\circ - \angle RPQ) =- \cos\angle RPQ$. Since $\sin^2 \angle RPQ + \cos^2 \angle RPQ = 1$, we have $\cos^2\angle RPQ = 1 - \left(\frac{7}{25}\right)^2 = \frac{576}{625}$.
Since $\angle RPQ$ is acute, we have $\cos\angle RPQ = \frac{24}{25}$, which gives us $\cos\angle RPS = -\cos\angle RPQ = \boxed{-\frac{24}{25}}$.
